 Genesis AudioDevice Logic – Audio Routing Modes
Mode Selection Based on ACTIVE/INACTIVE Flags
Audio routing behavior is determined by the ACTIVE status of GenesisAudioDevices at a site (location or logical group). There are three modes, defined as follows:
1. 🏢 Conference Mode – Full Collaboration
Condition:
All GenesisAudioDevices at the site are marked as ACTIVE.
Behavior:
Activates Conference Call Mode.
Devices share audio through a central conference bridge.
Suitable for multi-device, multi-user, or team-based environments.
Use Case:
Modern conference rooms with multiple devices needing synchronized audio participation.
2. 📞 Dial-In Mode – Single Device Control
Condition:
Exactly one GenesisAudioDevice at the site is ACTIVE, and all others are INACTIVE.
Behavior:
Engages Dial-In Behavior.
The ACTIVE device links directly to the audio sensor.
No linking logic for INACTIVE devices — they're ignored.
Use Case:
Legacy or simplified setups where a single device manages the audio (e.g., personal office dial-in).
3. 🎙️ Device Audio Mode – Isolated Operation
Condition:
All GenesisAudioDevices at the site are INACTIVE.
Behavior:
Devices use their own internal audio (microphone/speaker).
No audio sharing or linking.
Simplest mode – no dependencies.
Use Case:
Fallback operation or independent device use.
⚠️ Note: This behavior is pending confirmation in production.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Improved Audio Routing with Conference Mode Support
Previous Behavior:
When multiple Genesis audio devices were configured under a single site, initiating an audio call from the UI (for any camera under that site) would always route audio to the first added
Genesis audio device, regardless of its status.
New Behavior:
When an audio call is initiated and there are multiple active Genesis audio devices under the same site, the system will now initiate a conference mode.
In this mode:
All active Genesis audio devices and the Genesis-side operator will be connected in a conference.
This ensures collaborative communication across all active audio endpoints within the site.
Fallback Handling:
If none of the Genesis audio devices are active, or if the site has no Genesis audio devices configured:
The call will fall back to using the device's default audio, if supported by that particular device type.
NOTE:
- Genesis audio is configurable only if the user has the permission
- "Local mode" settings are not required (calls can be initiated via Genesis audio even if the local mode is disabled)
Steps to add an Genesis audio device under the site:
Step 1: Login to Genesis
Step 2: Navigate to the Configuration app in Genesis
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 3: Select the Site under which the Genesis audio device is need to be added
Step 4: Under the selected site, navigate to the "Devices" tab
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 5: Click on the "Add" button
Step 6: Under General Settings, click on "Type" which gives the list of devices that are available. Select "Genesis Audio"
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 7: Enter the desired name and click on "Discover"
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 8: Once the device is discovered, click on "Save"
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 9: A success pop up message "Device Created" will be displayed and the device will be added to the data table
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 10:  Verify if the added audio device is added by expanding the treeview under the site
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
NOTE: Use this Genesis Audio device credentials and configure the IP speaker.
Steps to initiate an Genesis Audio call request from the Salvo:
Step 1: Login  to the Genesis website
Step 2: Navigate to the Configuration app in the Genesis
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 3: Select the site in the tree view and right click to Expand the site
Step 4: Select the added Genesis audio device under the site in the tree view
Step 5: Verify if the "Active" toggle is enabled to indicate that the added Genesis audio device is active
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 6: Navigate to the Video viewer (Salvo) app
Step 7: Select the site in the tree view and expand the site
Step 8: Verify if the Genesis audio device is added under the selected site
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 9: Now drag and drop an sensor from the site into the video viewer (Salvo)
Step 10: Verify the mic symbol is enabled (red colour).
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 11: Click on the mic symbol, an audio call will be initiated
Step 12: Once the call is connected, the color of the mic will be changed from red to blue
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
Step 13: Click again on the mic to disconnect the call. Color of the mic will change from blue to red, once the call is disconnected.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000020645288/en
